9 An Act relating to discrimination; adopting certain
definition of anti-Semitism; stating purposes for use
10 of certain definition; construing provisions;
providing for codification; providing an effective
11 date; and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1911 of Title 25, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The State of Oklahoma hereby adopts the non-legally binding
19 Working Definition of Anti-Semitism adopted by the International
20 Holocaust Remembrance Alliance (IHRA) on May 26, 2016, including the
21 contemporary examples of anti-Semitism set forth therein,
22 exclusively as a tool and guide for training, education, and
23 recognizing and combating anti-Semitic hate crimes or discrimination
24 and for tracking and reporting anti-Semitic incidents in this state.
